type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#submissions"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Submissions"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#challenges"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Challenges"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#acceptance"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Acceptance"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This is an overview of the process by which Reputation scores in Colony are maintained."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For a complete description of the Reputation Mining process, see the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://colony.io/whitepaper.pdf"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"whitepaper"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h1","properties":{"id":"rationale-for-off-chain-reputation"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#rationale-for-off-chain-reputation","ariaLabel":"rationale for off chain reputation permalink","className":["md-heading-link"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Rationale for off-chain Reputation"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Events in Colony that affect reputation are numerous and expected to be frequent. The calculations for global reputation updates would be unreasonable to perform on-chain. However, Reputation doesn't "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"need"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to be on-chain, because reputation is entirely deterministic and calculated from on-chain events."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So, rather than calculating reputation scores on-chain, users submit to the colony contract a transaction  which contains their score, together with a proof that the score is consistent with the global state of reputation."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"reputation-mining-overview"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#reputation-mining-overview","ariaLabel":"reputation mining overview permalink","className":["md-heading-link"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Reputation Mining Overview"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The process of maintaining consensus over the global state of reputation is called "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Reputation Mining"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Reputation Mining resembles a proof-of-stake blockchain consensus protocol. Miners must put up a stake of the network token, CLNY, to participate in the reputation mining process, whereby the global state of reputation is calculated off-chain and submitted to the blockchain as a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"reputationRootHash"}]},{"type":"text","value":". In the case of honest submissions, the miner is rewarded reputation in the Meta Colony tagged with a special 'mining' skill. In the event of malicious activity, miners with false submission is punished by losing her stake."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"reputation-updates"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#reputation-updates","ariaLabel":"reputation updates permalink","className":["md-heading-link"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Reputation Updates"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"One feature of reputation that distinguish it from a token or cryptographic asset is that reputation cannot be transferred between accounts through a voluntary transaction. Rather, it is a number associated with an address, calculated from a well-defined set of on-chain events."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Reputation within a specific colony can only be earned and lost by completing tasks within the colony, through the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"/colonynetwork/whitepaper-tldr-objections-and-disputes/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"objections and disputes mechanism"}]},{"type":"text","value":", and in the case of the Meta Colony, through participation in the reputation mining process."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"reputation-root-hashes"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#reputation-root-hashes","ariaLabel":"reputation root hashes permalink","className":["md-heading-link"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Reputation Root Hashes"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Using a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Patricia-Tree"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Patricia Tree"}]},{"type":"text","value":", all updates to the global state of reputation are maintained on-chain with a single \"Reputation Root Hash\"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Reputation Root Hash is effectively a fingerprint for the network state (of reputation). It is calculated off-chain, but it represents the collection of all reputation-updating events that have occurred on the network, and even a single discrepancy in the complete history of reputational updates will result in a different Root Hash."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"the-reputation-mining-cycle"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#the-reputation-mining-cycle","ariaLabel":"the reputation mining cycle permalink","className":["md-heading-link"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"The Reputation Mining Cycle"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Reputation mining is a cyclic process in which multiple actors compete to verify the global reputation state."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The process works on an “innocent until proven guilty” principle: Although it’s infeasible for a valid hash to be proven true on-chain, it’s relatively straightforward for an invalid hash to be proven false. In the event that two submitted hashes differ, the false one can be fleshed out through an automated challenge process "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"on-chain"}]},{"type":"text","value":" that will eventually zero in on the exact on-chain events that differ between any two submitted hashes."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The reputation system depends on having at "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"at least one"}]},{"type":"text","value":" honest submission per cycle (as opposed to at least 51% of submissions as is the case in proof-of-work mining)."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"submissions"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#submissions","ariaLabel":"submissions permalink","className":["md-heading-link"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Submissions"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Each cycle begins with a submission window, in which all miners compete to submit a correct Root Hash to the network. The Root Hash must be calculated from the events stored in a Reputation Update Log, which contains a fixed list of updates to global reputation logged during the previous mining cycle."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A miner is eligible to submit a new Root Hash only if they stake an amount of CLNY. The amount of CLNY staked determines the number of times a miner can submit a Root Hash to the network during each submission window. Thus the greater the stake, the greater the likelihood that a miner will receive rewards from a successful submission."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"challenges"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#challenges","ariaLabel":"challenges permalink","className":["md-heading-link"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Challenges"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The complete challenge-response protocol is described in section 7.5.1 of the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://colony.io/whitepaper.pdf"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Colony whitepaper"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For the sake of legibility, the general process has been simplified below to describe a situation in which only two miners are participating in the challenge process, with one of them being a malicious actor:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If two different root hashes are submitted, it is assumed that one submission is honest. Therefore, one submission is false, and the miner that submitted an invalid hash must be punished."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In whichever submission is false, there must be one or more reputation update(s) inconsistent with the global state of reputation up until the current submission window."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Miners can submit a justification to the network that shows how a reputation update results in a Root Hash consistent with the last agreed upon Root Hash (of the previous cycle), and they can do so for each reputation update in the current cycle."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Both miners must provide such a justification to the network for each historical update until the discrepancy is found, at which point the correct hash can be calculated "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"on-chain"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Whichever miner is found to have performed the calculation incorrectly is punished by losing some of their CLNY stake."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"acceptance"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#acceptance","ariaLabel":"acceptance permalink","className":["md-heading-link"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Acceptance"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When a new Root Hash is accepted by the network, its corresponding Reputation Update Log is deleted from on-chain memory."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"All reputation events that occurred during the current cycle are 'frozen' as the new Reputation Update Log to be used by miners in the next cycle."}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}}},"project":{"slug":"colonynetwork","name":"colonyNetwork","logo":"img/colonyNetwork_color.svg","logoSmall":"img/logomark_colonyNetwork_blue.svg","repoUrl":"https://github.com/JoinColony/colonyNetwork","sectionOrder":["intro","docs","bug-bounty-program","whitepaper-tldr","interface"],"sectionTranslations":null,"sections":[{"name":"Doc